## ğŸ“¦ API Endpoints

### `POST /register/register-bot`

Registers or updates a bot product.

**Body Parameters:**

| Field               | Type     | Required | Description                        |
|--------------------|----------|----------|------------------------------------|
| botName            | string   | âœ…       | Name of the bot                    |
| botVersion         | string   | âœ…       | Version number                     |
| botDescription     | string   | âœ…       | Short description                  |
| botCategory        | string   | âœ…       | Category (e.g., moderation, music) |
| botLanguage        | string   | âœ…       | Programming language               |
| features           | string[] | Optional | List of features                   |
| licenseType        | string   | âœ…       | Free, Paid, or Subscription        |
| price              | number   | âœ…       | License price                      |
| currency           | string   | âœ…       | Currency code (e.g., USD)          |
| supportEmail       | string   | Optional | Email used for communication       |

Responds with a success message and optionally sends:
- A confirmation email to `supportEmail`
- A DM to the user (if Discord client is configured)

